WEBVTT



00:00:09.952 --> 00:00:13.248
Welcome to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast.

00:00:13.376 --> 00:00:17.472
Our mission is to develop fully devoted followers of Christ.

00:00:17.888 --> 00:00:27.552
If you're new to the podcast, our church is going through the entire book of Psalms, and on today's episode, we're excited to have Julie Haltawanger reading Psalm 144.

00:00:30.144 --> 00:00:32.704
I'm reading Psalms 144.

00:00:32.608 --> 00:00:42.656
I pray, speak to the Lord, my rock, who trains my hands for war, my fingers for battle. He is my loving God and my fortress, my stronghold, my deliverer.

00:00:42.176 --> 00:00:47.744
River, my shield and whom I take refuge, who subsides people under me.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:51.744
Lord, what are human beings that you care for them?

00:00:51.456 --> 00:00:52.896
Amir mortals?

00:00:52.768 --> 00:00:54.496
That you think of them?

00:00:54.400 --> 00:00:58.016
They are like breath, their days are like fleeting shadows.

00:00:57.856 --> 00:01:00.704
Part your heavens, Lord, and come down.

00:01:00.640 --> 00:01:07.648
Touch the mountains so they smoke. Send forth lightning and scatter the enemy. Shoot your arrows and root them.

00:01:07.680 --> 00:01:13.600
Reach down your hand from high, deliver me and rescue me from the mighty waters.

00:01:13.536 --> 00:01:17.376
From the hands of foreigners whose mouths are full of lies.

00:01:17.248 --> 00:01:23.136
whose right hands are deceitful. I sing a new song to you, my God.

00:01:23.008 --> 00:01:31.392
On this ten-stringed lyre, I will make music to you to the one who gives victory to the kings, who delivers his servant David.

00:01:31.232 --> 00:01:36.800
From the deadly sword deliver me, rescue me from the hands of foreigners.

00:01:38.208 --> 00:01:42.464
And his mouths are full of lies, whose right hands are deceitful.

00:01:42.272 --> 00:01:52.320
Then our sons in their youth will be like well-nurtured plants and our daughters will be like pillars carved to adorn a palace our barns will be filled with

00:01:51.840 --> 00:01:56.736
He filled with every kinds of provision. Our sheep were increased by thousands.

00:01:56.896 --> 00:02:06.944
By tens of thousands in our fields, our oxygen will draw heavy loads. There will be no breaching of walls, no going into captivity, no cries of distress.

00:02:06.464 --> 00:02:08.128
The stress in our streets.

00:02:07.744 --> 00:02:14.496
Blessed is the people whom this is true. Blessed is the Lord's people whose God is the Lord.

00:02:14.368 --> 00:02:16.320
A question for thought.

00:02:16.832 --> 00:02:23.520
Does humanity lead to the greater confidence before God? When do you feel more confident before God?

00:02:23.264 --> 00:02:25.088
And when do you feel the least?

00:02:24.960 --> 00:02:27.360
Thank you. I hope you have a blessed day.

00:02:35.232 --> 00:02:43.424
We hope this message was encouraging to you. If you would like this kind of content delivered directly to you, consider subscribing to our channel.

00:02:43.456 --> 00:02:52.928
If you'd like more information about our church, please visit us on the web at canopyroads.org. And thanks for listening to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast.
